Wash and dry all produce. Bring a large #pot of salted water to a boil. Halve, peel, and thinly slice @yellow onion{1}(peeled and thinly sliced) from pole to pole into strands. Core and seed @red bell pepper{1}, then cut into thin strips. Mince @parsley{1/4%ounce}. Place @whole peeled tomatoes{28%ounce} in a #medium bowl and break up with your hands into small pieces.

Heat @vegetable oil{4%tsp} in a large pan over medium-high heat. Add onion, bell pepper, and half the @Tuscan heat spice{2%tablespoon}. Cook, tossing, until lightly softened, ~{3-4%minutes}.

Remove sausage from casings. Add @sweet Italian pork sausage{18%ounce} and a large drizzle of oil to pan with veggies, breaking up meat into pieces. Cook, tossing occasionally, until sausage is cooked through and browned at edges, about ~{5%minutes}.

Once water boils, add @whole wheat spaghetti{12%ounce} to #pot. Cook, stirring occasionally, until al dente, ~{9-11%minutes}. Carefully scoop out and reserve 3 cups pasta cooking water, then drain.

Meanwhile, once sausage is browned, add tomatoes to pan. Season with @salt{}, @pepper{}, and remaining Tuscan heat spice, then give everything a stir. Bring to a boil, then lower heat and let simmer until pasta is done. After you've drained spaghetti, stir 2 cups pasta cooking water and @chicken stock concentrate{2} into pan. Continue simmering until slightly reduced, about ~{2%minutes}.

Add spaghetti to pan, tossing to coat.

> TIP: Add more pasta cooking water if needed to give sauce a loose consistency.

Stir in @butter{2%tablespoon}, half the parsley, and half the @Parmesan cheese{1/2%cup}. Season with salt and pepper. Divide between #bowls, then sprinkle with remaining parsley and Parmesan.